The paper deals with the integration of independent databases, which is a core topic in database management systems (cs.DB). The method proposed in the paper is based on abductive logic programming, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses model-theoretic analysis, which is a topic in mathematical logic (cs.LO). The implementation of the method is based on an abductive solver, which is a type of logic programming (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the soundness and completeness of the method, which are topics in software engineering (cs.SE).
